I have some projects / issue types that don't use components, so the component is hidden in the field configuration.  It seems that when the field configuration is set is set to hide the components field, then this JQL won't match any issues:
 {code}component is empty{code}

I can work around it with something like this:
{code}component is empty or ((project not in A and type not in B) or (project not in X and type not in Y) ...){code}
This makes for some complex JQL queries for my users to maintain, because I have a sizeable number of combinations of which projects and issue types have and do not have components.

I think it'd be handy if {code}component is empty{code} would also match issues where the component field is hidden.

h3. Steps to Reproduce:
# Create a copy of the *Default Workflow*;
# Create a *Workflow Scheme*;
# Associate the Workflow Scheme with the Workflow and with a Project;
# Modify the Workflow and add a property to the *Closed* step - e.g.: 
{noformat:borderStyle=dashed| borderColor=#6A8EB3 |bgColor=#F8F8F8}
jira.permission.work.denied = denied
{noformat}
# Publish the workflow draft;
# Transition an issue to *Closed* and add Time Spent during the transition.

h3. Desired Behavior:
* The issue would be transitioned to Closed;
* Logged work would be updated with the value added in the transition;
* It would not be possible to Log Work while the issue is *Closed*.

h3. Actual Behavior:
(/) The issue is transitioned to Closed;
(x) Logged work is not updated with the value added in the transition;
(/) It is not possible to Log Work while the issue is *Closed*.

The following also appears in the logs:
{noformat:borderStyle=dashed| borderColor=#6A8EB3 |bgColor=#F8F8F8}
2013-08-05 14:37:50,208 http-bio-8090-exec-20 INFO matheus 877x11135x1 1gd0it9 X.X.X.X /secure/IssueAction!default.jspa [atlassian.jira.security.WorkflowBasedPermissionManager] work granted by permission scheme but DENIED by workflow
{noformat}

Apparently, the issue is being transitioned to Closed _before_ JIRA updates the issue with the values from the transition.

